"22oz bottle. Pours an extremely dark brownish black with a 1/2 inch of khaki head. Some lacing. The aroma is earth, chocolate, charcoal, and some slight funk. The taste is a refreshing mix of chocolate, charcoal, floral hops, burnt coffee and some light rye. Chocolate and charcoal towards the finish with some floral hop notes and earth. Mouthfeel is light which surprised me a bit due to the color. Very little alcohol presence. Somewhat nutty as it warms. This is a very interesting beer to say the least. Light and crisp like a Kolsch but there is a fair amount of smoke and chocolate. Almost reminds me of a schwarzbier. Overall, a strange beer but I like it and would buy it again."
