"Pours a translucent very dark brown with billowing head of dense light brown foam. Rings of thick lace on the glass. Smell: floral and slightly spicy with rye graininess, background sweetness and the impression of coffee wafting from across a room. Taste: light sweet fruit flavors upfront, then a blip of roast and toffee, into a big spicy rye thing with a vaguely lemony finish. Light bodied upfront then really explodes...silky feel... far more luxurious than your usual Kolsch. Dry finish. Very tasty. Should have added as a Rye Beer."
